    "The central question of diagnostic excellence, from Improving Diagnosis in Health Care, is 'Could this reasoning be wrong, and what would I do to find out?' The protective habit is a metacognitive pause that names the disconfirming finding and the safety net, treating bias as a live bedside threat rather than a lecture topic.",
